Subject: Drop orphan SHiP-fork references whose source/header files
 were never committed

The shipdist-build branch of webbjm/acts references four SHiP-specific
files that were never committed to the tree, breaking the build:

  * src/SNDBuilder.cpp in Examples/Detectors/TGeoDetector/CMakeLists.txt
  * ActsExamples/TGeoDetector/SNDBuilder.hpp in Examples/Python/src/Detector.cpp
    (and the corresponding py::class_<SNDBuilder> Python binding block)
  * ActsExamples/Io/Root/RootSHiPParticleReader.hpp in Examples/Python/src/RootInput.cpp
    (the matching ACTS_PYTHON_DECLARE_READER call is already commented
    out upstream, so only the include needs to go)
  * ActsExamples/Io/Root/RootParticleReader2.hpp in Examples/Python/src/RootInput.cpp
    (and the corresponding ACTS_PYTHON_DECLARE_READER call)
  * ActsExamples/Io/Root/SHiPTrackWriter2.hpp in Examples/Python/src/RootOutput.cpp
    (and the corresponding ACTS_PYTHON_DECLARE_WRITER call)

Drop all of them. None of these symbols are referenced anywhere else in
the tree. The Strawtube classes were moved to Examples/Algorithms/SHiP/.

Remove this patch once the upstream fork either commits the missing
files or drops these references itself.
